WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.520
Is your data science project structure just a bunch of files in a folder?

00:00:03.520 --> 00:00:05.360
Let's fix that in 30 seconds.

00:00:05.360 --> 00:00:07.520
First, separate your data from your code.

00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:12.280
Use a raw folder for untouched datasets and a process folder for clean datasets.

00:00:12.280 --> 00:00:16.160
Here we have our Cordo documents for analysis and creating a report.

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:20.000
Here we also have a shell script, which processes individual reports.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.400
And we wrap it all up in a solid readme that explains what the project actually does.

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:29.559
You can do things like add a models folder, a source folder for reusable functions, requirements.txt

00:00:29.559 --> 00:00:30.680
file.

00:00:30.680 --> 00:00:34.919
Cookie Cutter Data Science offers a lot of great guidance on structuring your data science

00:00:34.919 --> 00:00:35.919
projects.

00:00:35.919 --> 00:00:38.040
How do you improve your data science project structure?

00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:39.279
Let us know in the comments below.

